comment.body:
@caryoscelus: Thanks for the explanation. 
Damn, I used ZeroMe Unfuck to change hubs and it reported I was fully transitioned to KaffieHub and off torrents hub.

@Krixano: "people tend to stay with the "official" zites more for some reason." Network effect: there just aren't enough people on ZeroNet to support multiple social sites.

@caryoscelus: My theory: we all have only a limited amount of energy & attention for thinking and researching seriously. We can't think about & research seriously absolutely *everything* in life (because there are literally millions of variables) so we concentrate our effort on a few things we feel are most important to us. That means on all the other things in life we are reliant on others and on whatever info about it stuck in our minds over the years from casual exposure. Consequently we are *all* "trusting idiots" on many issues in life. It's just a question of *which* issues.
.
So for the people clicking on ads, marketing analysis & manipulation just isn't one of the issues they focus on. At least until "casual exposure", e.g. a big news story like Cambridge Analytica, might, *might*, register and impact their feelings on it.
